cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.AL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with scheduling challenges in modern data centers and proposes algorithms for efficient scheduling of highly parallel data flows. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on communication patterns in data flows. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with optimizing job-level performance objectives in data centers. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes algorithms for scheduling coflows. 
- cs.AL (Algorithms) is also a possible category as the paper focuses on developing and evaluating algorithms for coflow scheduling.
